<font color="#FF0000">A LITTLE STORY</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26  3:37:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I&quot;m 49 yrs old now,its been twenty odd years since i was in VietNam,in may of 1971,while patroling in a area with the 11th armoured cav,we ran into a very large mine,at that instant I lost my life,was reborn 8 months later in camp zama,Japan,the medical staff was wonderful<br>
I was in a coma for my whole stay in japan,not until now a realize how close i came to dying,i have had a blank of what happend to me during my recuperation and transfer to a state side hospital,looking at my medical records now,I know what a miracle it was to have been in the hands of the nurses in triage in vietnam,I had massive tissue loss,head trauma(very large hole in the frontal lobe)<br>
recuperation has been a very long process for me,relearned how to walk,talk,eat,everything that I learned when still a child,I was retired from the military with a 100% disability,I have lived most of my  adult life in anger,depression,drug abuse,in and out of hospitals,divorced,not played well with others,attempted suicide so many times,that the v.a.hospital as on open policy on me,this were the good times<br>
but guys,its not all bad news,which brings me to the point,I'm presently a member of a committe that put on a concert every year for Vietnam Veterans(Nam Jam)this focus is nurses that served in VietNam,we are deeply and humbly honored,that in a small way we can show our appreciation to those nurses that touched our lifes,we also have a museum dedicated to memorabilia and photos and other momentos that are contributed by our members of<br>
by the way is the largest gathering of VietNam vets in Arizona,last year,we had over 40,000 vets and their families attend,members of the VIetNam Of America,have help to form a educational committe of vietnam vets and the Vietnamese communitty to go to high schools and speak about our expiriences,ita been a very healing expirience,I'm on the way,guys,please be gentle with yourself,remember that VietNam was the best and worst of our lifes<br>
our friends that were lost,would want for us,to learned and became teachers to others,never again,my family and I,love you deeply.
<p><code>-- Borregos@aol.com  (SFC.Hugo E Benavente) </code><p>


